The sample size was computed with the following formula proposed to determine the reasonable sample size for seeing a difference between the means of two samples. Considering β = 0.20, α = 0.05, an anticipated effect size (d) = 0.70, and group ratio (r) = 1, an optimal sample size of approximately 33 subjects per group was calculated. However, we selected 36 patients in each group, considering 10% sample attrition.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
